article.description: Ta'Shia Phillips scored 15 points and grabbed 21 rebounds to lead Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) to a 74-59 win over St. Bonaventure on Sunday afternoon.
article.headline: Xavier holds 50-22 rebounding advantage in rout of St. Bonaventure
article.linkText: No. 21 Xavier owns boards, St. Bonaventure
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Ta'Shia Phillips scored 15 points and grabbed 21 rebounds to lead Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) to a 74-59 win over St. Bonaventure on Sunday afternoon.

It was the Musketeers' (19-4, 7-0 Atlantic 10) 10th straight victory.

Tudy Reed added 15 points, including five on consecutive possessions to cap a 10-0 run with 15:04 left that put Xavier in control.

Dana Mitchell led St. Bonaventure (15-6, 4-2) with 11 points, and Katelyn Murray and Jessica Jenkins each scored 10.

April Phillips added 15 points and 13 rebounds for Xavier, which outrebounded the Bonnies 50-22, including 21 offensive rebounds that led to 23 second-chance points.
